    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Take your chicken out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 mins)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-sweet-and-sour-chicken/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-sweet-and-sour-chicken/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chicken </strong>and<strong> pepper strips</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until the chicken is starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-sweet-and-sour-chicken/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, combine your <strong>cornflour</strong> and <strong>tomato ketchup </strong>in a small bowl with your <strong>soy sauce</strong>,<strong> rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>sweet & sour sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-sweet-and-sour-chicken/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has browned, add your<strong> ginger & garlic paste</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-sweet-and-sour-chicken/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>sweet & sour sauce</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>sweet & sour chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-sweet-and-sour-chicken/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, squeeze your pouch[es] of <strong>cooked long grain rice</strong> to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es] (just a little!) and <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two or more pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-sweet-and-sour-chicken/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sweet & sour chicken</strong> on top of the<strong> cooked rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
